Poppy modifications
-------------------

Modifications and additions made by Poppy contributors are released under the
same license as the file they modify (AGPL-3.0 for app code, MIT for the UI
framework crates). No re-licensing of upstream code is performed.

Poppy-specific changes are limited to:

  - Rebranding of the OSS channel from "warp-oss" to "poppy" (binary name,
    bundle identifier, app metadata, channel state, autoupdate paths,
    Windows packaging scripts).
  - Replacement of the OSS channel icon (`app/channels/oss/icon/no-padding/`)
    with a poppy flower drawing.
  - Removal of upstream-specific GitHub Actions infrastructure
    (issue templates, docubot, release pipelines) that does not apply
    to a community fork.
  - A minimal Windows CI workflow (`.github/workflows/build-windows.yml`)
    and a stub installer pipeline (`.github/workflows/release-stub.yml`).
  - Documentation rebranding (README, CONTRIBUTING, FAQ, SECURITY, POPPY.md).
  - Disabling of cloud-facing default features (telemetry / Sentry crash
    reporting / hosted-agent surface) for the OSS channel build, per the
    project's de-cloudification goal.

Trademarks
----------

"Warp" is a trademark of Warp Inc. Poppy uses neither the Warp name nor the
Warp logo as its product identity. The string "warp" appears in this
repository where it refers to upstream code paths, settings paths, or library
crate names that we have intentionally left unchanged for compatibility
(e.g. user data lives in `%APPDATA%\warp\Warp\` so a Warp → Poppy swap
preserves user configuration).

